The paper proposes a novel approach for sparse representation learning in reinforcement learning, which involves adapting tile coding into a deep learning setting. This makes it likely that the paper would be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper applies the proposed method to control problems in robotics (cs.RO), which further supports the likelihood of these categories. The paper also mentions theoretical guarantees and the absence of additional training parameters, which suggests a potential fit for neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY) sub-categories.
